Saudi Telecom, Global Investment: Persian Gulf Equity Preview

-- B y   M o u r a d   H a r o u t u n i a n
-- 
2011-09-05T05:44:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-05/saudi-telecom-global-investment-persian-gulf-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in Persian Gulf markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and prices are from the last close.  Dubai’s  DFM General Index (DFMGI)  fell 0.6 percent on the first day
of trading after the Islamic Eid Al Fitr holiday. Saudi Arabia’s
 Tadawul All Share Index (SASEIDX)  gained 0.8 percent.  Global Investment House KSCC (GLOBAL)  : The Kuwait-based
investment bank, which restructured $1.73 billion of debt in
2009, started initial talks with creditors on the possibility of
extending debt repayments, Al-Qabas reported today, without
saying where it obtained the information. The shares soared 8.9
percent to 30.5 fils.  Saudi Telecom Co. (STC)  : Saudi Arabia’s largest
telephone company by market value had its price estimate reduced
to 45.10 riyals from 50.90 riyals at Nomura Holdings Inc. The
shares were unchanged at 34.2 riyals.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mourad Haroutunian in Riyadh at 
 mharoutunian@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Shaji Mathew at 
 shajimathew@bloomberg.net  